1. What is the difference between == and .equals() in Java?

   In Java, the equals() method and the == operator are used to compare objects. The main difference is that string equals() method compares the content equality of two strings while the == operator compares the reference or memory location of objects in a heap, 
   whether they point to the same location or not.

